        <LEXMeaning Id="001286001001000" IsBiblicalTerm="M" EntryCode="26.14" Indent="0">
          <LEXDomains>
            <LEXDomain>Psychological Faculties</LEXDomain>
          </LEXDomains>
          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-06-01 10:14:00" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>the psychological faculty of understanding, reasoning, thinking, and deciding</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>mind</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In some languages there is no noun such as English mind, and therefore one must use a verb expression meaning ‘to think,’ ‘to reason,’ or ‘to understand,’ depending upon the particular context. In some languages the closest equivalent of ‘mind’ may be a figurative extension of a term meaning ‘head,’ but more often than not, thinking is regarded as being in some other part of the body, for example, ‘heart’ or ‘liver.’</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
          </LEXSenses>
